power relations. Building on this approach, this volume analyses the relational dynamics affecting Tunisian associations after the fall of the authoritarian regime in 2011 and their implications for the changing political order. Findings show two main interrelated trends: the nationwide professionalization of local associations and the localized networking strategies of various socio-political categories crossing the associational sector. The book shows how their members understand the standardization of local associations as a strategy to have guaranteed access to the public sphere and, therefore, to influence the changing political order.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil societyzTunisia. 0aPolitical participationzTunisia. 4aContemporary Society. 4aCultural Studies. 4aInterdisciplinary Studies. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civil Rights.2bisacsh  aTunisia, civil society, associations, international donors, politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048555956?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555956zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degr